  ----------- http://modulaframework.org -----------

Features/Roadmap
---------
 - Completely module based Content Management System
 - Fine-grained hierarchical permissions system based on Access Control Lists
 - All system events hookable via the Event Notification Module
 - Module system based on MVC design principles
 - Completely OOP design
 - Security features such as SSL, cross site scripting prevention, session hijacking prevention, cross site forgery protection for all forms, output buffer regex filtering for fail-safe filtering of potentionally sensitive information and extremely high entropy hashing algorithms provide an extremely secure environment for even the most secure websites
 - Template based views with hierarchical-style inheritance. I.e, reusable custom controls
 - Themeing system with simplified markup for quick theme building
 - Ruby-on-rails-like URI Routing system for unlimited routing patterns based on regular expressions
 - 'Intelligent' caching system for high traffic sites and or digg/slashdot effects
 - Plugable database driver, allows for any kind of data storage, whether it be flat file, PDO or mySQLi etc
 - General purpose libraries for various kinds of tasks such as image processing, file manipulation, file uploads, inter-site communications etc
 - Default front end based on jQueryUI components to give a rich user experience
 - 'Market Place' for installing and upgrading installed modules, security features include module signing and Developer authentication

Plus much more!
